<p>

A Steam update has just been released. The next time you restart Steam, the update will take effect. Here are the details on what is included:<br/><ul style="padding-bottom: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><li>Added support for "trickle update", which will allow updates to games to be delivered over time before they are activated.</li><br/><li>Optimizations in Steam targeted at reducing CPU and memory load on some systems.</li><br/><li>Progress dialog always shows now during startup.</li><br/><li>Fixed handling of cache fingerprint mismatch on reconnect</li><br/><li>Fixed case which would cause the preloader ignoring errors to send extra messages to the Steam servers.</li><br/><li>Fixed bug in Steam that would cause cache to be validated too often when Steam started. This would cause hard drive thrashing.</li><br/><li>Fixed a potential lockup case and access violation case in Steam.</li><br/></ul><br/></p>
